
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-psenak-mt-ospf-01.txt'>
    <title>"MT-OSPF: Multi Topology (MT) Routing in OSPF", Peter Psenak</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-psenak-mt-ospf-01.txt</link>
    <description>This draft describes the extension to OSPF in order to define independent IP topologies called Multi-Topologies (MTs). The MT extension can be used for computing different paths for different classes of service, in-band management network or incongruent topologies for unicast and multicast. M-ISIS describes a similar mechanism for ISIS. This draft also describes an optional extension of Multi-topologies whereby some links might be excluded from the default topology.</description>
    <dc:date>2004-08-18T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
